sentences: Intruder released three full-length albums and one EP from 1987 to 1991 before splitting up in 1992.
Intruder released three full-length albums and one EP from 1987 to 1991 before splitting up in 1992.
The band was originally formed in 1984 under the name "Transgresser".
They released demos in 1984 and 1986 (which would later appear on a re-release of their debut album).
They released their debut album Live to Die in 1987 as a four-piece band in the speed metal vein.
The band signed with Metal Blade Records in 1989.
Intruder released their second album, A Higher Form of Killing, in 1989 as a five-piece band.
Intruder released the very rare Escape from Pain EP in 1990.
In 1991 Intruder released their final full-length album Psycho Savant.
After five years of releases and touring, the group disbanded in 1992.
Since 2002, the group has reunited from time to time.
They performed at the Classic Metal Fest in Ohio, 2002, and had a headlining spot at the Headbangers Open Air in Germany.
They also played the Keep It True festival in Germany in 2007 and a reunion show in their home town of Nashville in November, 2011, in honor of the 20th anniversary of Psycho Savant.

In 2004, the band re-released their 1987 debut album Live to Die through Hellion Records with six bonus tracks.
This will be the first time the original Metal Blade lineup will have recorded together since 1991.
2017 was the 30th anniversary of the band.
After a few years on hiatus, Intruder announced a reunion on their Facebook page on October 16, 2019, and they were be planning to play some shows in 2020, including that year's Headbangers Open Air.
